item.title: GADBench: Revisiting and Benchmarking Supervised Graph Anomaly Detection
item.description: With a long history of traditional Graph Anomaly Detection (GAD) algorithms and recently popular Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), it is still not clear (1) how they perform under a standard comprehensive setting, (2) whether GNNs outperform traditional algorithms such as tree ensembles, and (3) their efficiency on large-scale graphs.

item.title: grenedalf: population genetic statistics for the next generation of pool sequencing
